@agh4sea just dropped new policy that Andrew Grant Houston will implement as mayor. We’ll be talking through some of this policy, starting with this post on the proposed “office of the urban forest”. This post explains why Seattle would benefit from such an office that is dedicated to managing Seattle’s forestry. The points made in this post are just the tip of the iceberg- the topic of our environment is vast, and we are a city known for our nature.
Tomorrow we’ll have another post on the office of urban forestry, with more policy information. If you want to read the policy yourself, go to agh4sea.com

